                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.7961/59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-06T14:00:00-03:00"
                            >October 6, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>512. President Vargas has ruled that effective today all pilots for aircraft of
                    Brazilian registry, with one exception, must be native born Brazilians. This
                    eliminates the German pilots who are naturalized Brazilians flying for the
                    Syndicato Condor and the Vasp Rio de Janeiro–São Paulo Line. The exception is
                    the Varig Line in Rio Grande do Sul which is given to February 1, 1941 to
                    comply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
